[b]Regime Detector[/b] identifies the current market regime using an adaptive MA-zone engine, filtered by a higher-timeframe gate and supported by advanced signal management.

[b]What it does[/b]

The indicator defines zones around moving averages and classifies price location relative to those zones as Bull, Bear, or Neutral. An adaptive core engine adjusts sensitivity based on recent volatility. A higher-timeframe gate prevents signals from firing against the broader trend context.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Adaptive regime engine[/b] — Sensitivity adjusts to recent volatility; reduces false regime changes in choppy conditions
[*][b]Multi-timeframe gate[/b] — Higher-timeframe regime acts as a filter for chart-level signals
[*][b]Zone visualization[/b] — Up to 500 lines and 100 boxes for dynamic zone rendering on the chart
[*][b]Signal management[/b] — Controls signal frequency and transition logic to minimize noise
[/list]

[b]Alerts[/b]
All alerts fire only on confirmed bar close by default (configurable via "Alerts only on bar close" toggle).

Choose one of two alert modes — do not enable both simultaneously, or each event will fire twice:

[b]Named alertconditions[/b] (individual events via the Create Alert dialog):
[list]
[*][b]RDP Long Entry[/b] — high-confidence long regime entry
[*][b]RDP Short Entry[/b] — high-confidence short regime entry
[*][b]RDP Exit Long[/b] — exit signal for an active long position
[*][b]RDP Exit Short[/b] — exit signal for an active short position
[*][b]RDP Any High Confidence[/b] — any high-confidence entry in either direction
[*][b]RDP Regime Change[/b] — regime classification has changed
[*][b]RDP HTF Divergence[/b] — higher-timeframe regime diverges from chart
[*][b]RDP Regime Weakening[/b] — current regime showing weakening signals
[*][b]RDP Volatility Compression[/b] — volatility entering a compressed state
[*][b]RDP Volatility Expansion[/b] — volatility breaking out of compression
[*][b]SSA Custom Alert (Builder)[/b] — fires when the SSA builder conditions are met
[*][b]SSA Long[/b] — SSA long event triggered
[*][b]SSA Short[/b] — SSA short event triggered
[*][b]SSA Strong Long[/b] — SSA strong long event triggered
[*][b]SSA Strong Short[/b] — SSA strong short event triggered
[*][b]SSA Super Long[/b] — SSA super long event triggered
[*][b]SSA Super Short[/b] — SSA super short event triggered
[/list]

[b]Unified webhook (alternative)[/b]: use the "any alert() function call" rule to receive all events in a single structured message — suitable for bots and automation. Contains regime, confidence, HTF agreement, and signal quality fields.

